owl:AnnotationProperty.terms:description: Description may include but is not limited to: an abstract, a table of contents, a graphical representation, or a free-text account of the resource.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Description

owl:AnnotationProperty.terms:description: Recommended practice is to describe the date, date/time, or period of time as recommended for the property Date, of which this is a subproperty.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Date of formal issuance of the resource.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Date Issued

owl:AnnotationProperty.terms:description: Recommended practice is to identify the license document with a URI. If this is not possible or feasible, a literal value that identifies the license may be provided.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A legal document giving official permission to do something with the resource.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: License

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: An alias in which the alias exhibits true synonymy. Example: ornithine cycle is an exact synonym of urea cycle
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: has_exact_synonym

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: An alias in which the alias is related the primary class name, but not necessarily broader or narrower. Example: cytochrome bc1 complex is a related synonym of ubiquinol-cytochrome-c reductase activity; virulence is a related synonym of pathogenesis
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: has_related_synonym

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation between a class and an alias term.
Note that this should be a super-property of hasRelatedSynonym, hasExactSynonym etc; however, we cannot state this and remain in OWL-DL
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: has_synonym

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The range of skos:altLabel is the class of RDF plain literals.
skos:prefLabel, skos:altLabel and skos:hiddenLabel are pairwise disjoint properties.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: alternative label
owl:AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: An alternative lexical label for a resource.
owl:AnnotationProperty.skos:example: Acronyms, abbreviations, spelling variants, and irregular plural/singular forms may be included among the alternative labels for a concept. Mis-spelled terms are normally included as hidden labels (see skos:hiddenLabel).

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: definition
owl:AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: A statement or formal explanation of the meaning of a concept.

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A resource has no more than one value of skos:prefLabel per language tag, and no more than one value of skos:prefLabel without language tag.
The range of skos:prefLabel is the class of RDF plain literals.
skos:prefLabel, skos:altLabel and skos:hiddenLabel are pairwise disjoint properties.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: preferred label
owl:AnnotationProperty.skos:definition: The preferred lexical label for a resource, in a given language.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Connects a biological entity to its taxon of origin.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: in taxon

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Is member of is a mereological relation between a item and a collection.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: member of

owl:ObjectProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: A relationship that holds between two entities in which the processes executed by the two entities are causally connected.
owl:ObjectProperty.obo:IAO_0000116: This relation and all sub-relations can be applied to either (1) pairs of entities that are interacting at any moment of time (2) populations or species of entity whose members have the disposition to interact (3) classes whose members have the disposition to interact.
owl:ObjectProperty.obo:IAO_0000232: Note that this relationship type, and sub-relationship types may be redundant with process terms from other ontologies. For example, the symbiotic relationship hierarchy parallels GO. The relations are provided as a convenient shortcut. Consider using the more expressive processual form to capture your data. In the future, these relations will be linked to their cognate processes through rules.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: interacts with

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Homologous pairwise relation between sequence units (e.g.: genes, proteins or gene regions). For example, A Gene(A) hasHomolog Gene(B). This property can be materialized or inferred by applying a logical rule.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has homolog

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Property that permits to define the membership of a cluster of homologs or a sequence unit to a clusters of homologs.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has homologous member

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Inverse property of inDataset. It permits to retrieve the clusters or homology relations included in a particular dataset.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has homology data

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Property that provides the dataset associated with a gene tree node
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: in dataset

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Inverse of has homologous member. This property permits to find the cluster in which a cluster or sequence unit is included.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is homologous member

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: It states a protein that functionally interacts with another one, a pairwise relationship.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: functionally interacts with

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: It states a protein-protein functional interaction score.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has functional interaction score

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: It states a network image of interactions among proteins (e.g. from STRING database). The image is composed of a neighborhood surrounding one or more proteins.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has network image

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: It states a protein-protein physical interaction score.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has physical interaction score

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: It states a protein that is part of or contained in the subject.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has protein

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: It states a protein that physically interacts with another one, a pairwise relationship.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: physically interacts with

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A concept that classifies this resource.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: classified with

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A resource that is replaced by this resource.
has part is a transitive, reflexive and antisymmetric relation between a whole and itself or a whole and its part.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has part
is in scheme
owl:ObjectProperty.skos:definition: Relates a resource (for example a concept) to a concept scheme in which it is included.
owl:ObjectProperty.skos:scopeNote: A concept may be a member of more than one concept scheme.

owl:DatatypeProperty.terms:description: Description may include but is not limited to: an abstract, a table of contents, a graphical representation, or a free-text account of the resource.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: An account of the resource.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Description

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The mean degree of the node in the network.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: average node degree

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Smith-Waterman alignment bit-score.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: bit-score

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The coexpression score is derived from similar pattern of mRNA expression measured by DNA arrays and similar technologies.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: coexpression score

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The combined score is computed by combining the probabilities from the different evidence channels and corrected for the probability of randomly observing an interaction. The combined score is computed from the partial scores (e.g. fusion score, experimental score).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: combined score

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The database score is derived from curated data of various databases.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: database score

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The number of edges in the network.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: edge amount

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The expected number of edges based on the nodes degrees.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: expected edge amount

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The experimental score is derived from experimental data, such as, affinity chromatography.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: experimental score

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The file format (e.g. png, svg).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: format

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The gene fusion score is derived from fused proteins in other species.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: gene fusion score

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The average local clustering coefficient.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: edge amount

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The neighborhood score is computed from the inter-gene nucleotide count.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: gene neighborhood score

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The style of edges in the network: evidence, confidence, actions
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: network flavor

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The network type: functional or physical
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: network type

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The number of proteins in the network, that are representend with nodes.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: protein amount

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The partial scores used to compute the combined scores.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: partial score

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The cooccurence score of the phyletic profile that is derived from similar absence/presence patterns of genes.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: phylogenetic profile score

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: P-value for statistical significance. For example, in STRING DB, the significance of the network having more interactions than expected.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: p-value

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The image resolution as a qualitative value (e.g. high resolution).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: resolution

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: The textmining score is derived from the co-occurrence of gene/protein names in abstracts.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: text mining score

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A easy to remember identifier for a UniProtKB entry, but it is not a stable identifier and should not be used by programs to identify entries.
A rememberable string that can be used to find entries, not a stable identifier!
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Mnemonic

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000112: A heart, a human, a fly, a microarray.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A material entity is an entity that exists in full during the length of time of its existence, persists through this time while maintaining its identity and has no temporal parts. For example a heart, a human, a fly, a microarray.
owl:Class.efo:source_definition: An independent continuant [snap:IndependentContinuant] that is spatially extended whose identity is independent of that of other entities and can be maintained through time. Note: Material entity [snap:MaterialEntity] subsumes object [snap:Object], fiat object part [snap:FiatObjectPart], and object aggregate [snap:ObjectAggregate], which assume a three level theory of granularity, which is inadequate for some domains, such as biology.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: material entity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class represents homology relations among sequence units (e.g genes, proteins or gene regions).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: homology relation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A living being, such as an animal, a plant, a bacterium, or a fungus., Any individual living (or previously living) being. Example: animal, human being. An organim can be associated to a taxon such as "Homo Sapiens", NCBI taxonomy identifier: 9606.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Organism

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: protein or DNA sequence as a unit of comparison
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sequence unit

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A network image of interactions among proteins, that illustrates a neighborhood surrounding one or more proteins.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: network image

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Even in the absence of annotated proteins (e.g. in novel genomes) databases such as STRING can tell if the subset of proteins is functionally related, that is, if it is enriched in interactions in comparison to the background proteome-wide interaction distribution.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: protein-protein interaction enrichment

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Temporary, non-covalent binding between protein molecules. Protein-protein interactions occur as a result of intermolecular physical forces and spatial complementation between domains or motifs. This interaction can be either homotypic or heterotypic and effect protein structure, conformation, and function.[source: NCIT]
owl:Class.rdfs:label: protein-protein interaction

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class to define a set of any type of score values.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: score

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A concept used to classify resources.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Concept

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Metadata for a life science database.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Database (description of)

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An element of a taxonomy for classifying life forms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Taxon

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A database is a data store such as relational, hierarchical and graph databases.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: database
Concept Scheme
owl:Class.skos:definition: A set of concepts, optionally including statements about semantic relationships between those concepts.
owl:Class.skos:example: Thesauri, classification schemes, subject heading lists, taxonomies, 'folksonomies', and other types of controlled vocabulary are all examples of concept schemes. Concept schemes are also embedded in glossaries and terminologies.
owl:Class.skos:scopeNote: A concept scheme may be defined to include concepts from different sources.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Integrated resource of protein families, domains and functional sites
KEGG: Kyoto Encyclopedia of Genes and Genomes
Reactome - a knowledgebase of biological pathways and processes
Simple Modular Architecture Research Tool; a protein domain database

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: STRING is a database of known and predicted protein-protein interactions. The interactions include direct (physical) and indirect (functional) associations; they stem from computational prediction, from knowledge transfer between organisms, and from interactions aggregated from other (primary) databases.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: STRING database

rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000112: PMID:19696660 in contrast to the in-vivo data AT-III increased significantly from 113.5% at baseline to 117% after 4 days (n = 10, P-value= 0.02; Table 2).
rdf:Description.obo:IAO_0000115: A quantitative confidence value that represents the probability of obtaining a result at least as extreme as that actually obtained, assuming that the actual value was the result of chance alone.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: p-value

rdf:Description.terms:description: Changes in version imply substantive changes in content rather than differences in format. This property is intended to be used with non-literal values. This property is an inverse property of Is Version Of.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource that is a version, edition, or adaptation of the described resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Has Version

rdf:Description.terms:description: Changes in version imply substantive changes in content rather than differences in format. This property is intended to be used with non-literal values. This property is an inverse property of Has Version.
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A related resource of which the described resource is a version, edition, or adaptation.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Is Version Of
